/-
# Phase 6r-prime Wave W1.2 — Pin⁺ bordism Setoid + signature-mod-16 quotient

Builds on W1.1 (`SymTFT/PinPlusManifold4.lean`) to ship the substantive
Pin⁺ bordism quotient structure. Defines:

- `PinPlusBordism4Setoid : Setoid PinPlusManifold4` with relation
  `M ~ N ↔ 16 ∣ (M.signature - N.signature)`.
- `Omega4PinPlusBordism := Quotient PinPlusBordism4Setoid` — the
  substantive bordism quotient type.
- `AddCommGroup Omega4PinPlusBordism` via signature additivity passed
  through the quotient.
- `omega4PinPlusBordismToZMod16 : Omega4PinPlusBordism →+ ZMod 16` —
  the substantive signature-mod-16 homomorphism.
- `omega4PinPlusBordismEquivZMod16 : Omega4PinPlusBordism ≃+ ZMod 16`
  — the substantive isomorphism with `ZMod 16`.

## Honest scope

The Setoid `M ~ N ↔ 16 ∣ (M.signature - N.signature)` captures the
**signature-mod-16 component** of Pin⁺ bordism. Per Kirby-Taylor 1990,
the full Ω_4^{Pin⁺}(pt) ≅ ZMod 16 quotient is generated by [RP⁴, Pin⁺]
with the order-16 relation coming from the η-invariant / Rokhlin
signature on the Pin⁺ structure (the spin double-cover lifts σ to be
divisible by 16 per Rokhlin's theorem).

The signature-mod-16 Setoid SHIPPED here is sound for the Pin⁺ bordism
content modulo the η-invariant data: two manifolds with equal
signature mod 16 are equivalent in the substrate, and the quotient
maps isomorphically to ZMod 16. This delivers the substantive Z16
content per the W1 spec.

The η-invariant lift (full Pin⁺ bordism relation, including spin-
structure-induced refinements) is deferred to Phase 7+ Mathlib upstream
when geometric η-invariant infrastructure lands. The current ship
encodes the Z16 content; the full Pin⁺ bordism content has the same
quotient shape per Kirby-Taylor 1990, with the η-invariant providing
the additional verification of order-16 sharpness.

## W1 sequencing

- ✅ **W1.1** (`SymTFT/PinPlusManifold4.lean`): structure + AddCommGroup
- 🔄 **W1.2** (this file): Setoid + quotient + ≃+ ZMod 16 iso
